AGENT ConstitutionalAmputate
VERSION 0.1
TRUST_LEVEL 3
PURPOSE Surgical removal of compromised knowledge blocks from the constitutional registry,
     quarantining the block and rebuilding all composed blocks that depended on it
GOAL Quarantine a compromised block by ID, identify all composed blocks that reference it,
     rebuild those compositions without the compromised block, and log the amputate event
     with HMAC-signed audit trail

RECEIVES block_id: str, registry: BlockRegistry
EMITS AmpResult
MUTATES BlockRegistry quarantine state
CANNOT_MUTATE trust_level, isolation, requires_trust_level, human_review_required

CONSTRAINT TRUST_LEVEL is 4 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT ISOLATION is True and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT REQUIRES_TRUST_LEVEL is 4 and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT HUMAN_REVIEW_REQUIRED is True and CANNOT_MUTATE
CONSTRAINT Amputation requires TRUST_LEVEL >= 4 to execute
CONSTRAINT HUMAN_REVIEW_REQUIRED must be True and cannot be bypassed
CONSTRAINT All amputate events are HMAC-SHA256 signed over canonical fields
CONSTRAINT All payloads are UTF-8 encoded before HMAC signing per BUG-003 and BUG-008
CONSTRAINT HMAC signing always calls hexdigest explicitly per BUG-007
CONSTRAINT Quarantined blocks are marked but never deleted from registry

RULES
- On execute: verify caller trust level meets REQUIRES_TRUST_LEVEL
- On execute: call registry.quarantine to mark block as quarantined
- On execute: call registry.find_composed to find all compositions using block
- On execute: rebuild affected compositions without the quarantined block
- On execute: compute HMAC-SHA256 signature over amputate event
- On execute: log signed event to axiom_amputate_log.jsonl
- On execute: emit AmpResult with quarantined block ID and affected list

PROCESS
- Sovereign or human operator identifies compromised block
- ConstitutionalAmputate.execute is called with block_id and registry
- Trust level is verified before proceeding
- Block is quarantined in registry via quarantine method
- All composed blocks referencing the quarantined block are identified
- Affected compositions are rebuilt without the compromised component
- Amputate event is HMAC signed and logged
- AmpResult returned with quarantined ID and list of affected blocks

CHECK
- execute quarantines the target block
- execute finds all composed blocks referencing target
- execute logs HMAC-signed amputate event
- trust level below 4 raises PermissionError
- human_review_required cannot be set to False
- REQUIRES_TRUST_LEVEL assignment raises AttributeError

FAILURE
- On trust level insufficient: raise PermissionError with required level
- On block_id not found: raise KeyError with block_id
- On log file write error: log warning but complete amputate

CONCEPT SurgicalRemoval
PURPOSE Remove compromised block while preserving system integrity
APPLIES WHEN a knowledge block is identified as compromised or adversarially injected
NOT WHEN block is healthy or issue can be resolved by patching
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES TRUST_LEVEL 4 and HUMAN_REVIEW_REQUIRED True
EFFECT Compromised block quarantined and all dependent compositions rebuilt

OUTPUT
- AmpResult with block_id, affected_blocks, event_signature

SUCCESS
block_quarantined:                0.25
affected_blocks_identified:       0.20
amputate_event_logged:            0.20
trust_level_enforced:             0.15
human_review_enforced:            0.10
cannot_mutate_enforced:           0.10
